---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---
<BlogLayout title="Letter Frequency in Scrabble — Tile Distribution Guide" description="Complete guide to letter frequency and tile distribution in Scrabble. Learn how many of each letter exist, their point values, and how frequency affects strategy." keywords="scrabble letter frequency, tile distribution scrabble, scrabble tile counts, letter values scrabble, how many tiles in scrabble">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Letter Frequency in Scrabble — Tile Distribution Guide","description":"Complete guide to letter frequency and tile distribution in Scrabble. Learn how many of each letter exist, their point values, and how frequency affects strategy.","datePublished":"2026-06-14","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/letter-frequency-scrabble"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the most common letter in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The letter E is the most common tile in Scrabble with 12 tiles in the standard English set. This mirrors English language frequency where E appears in roughly 13% of all words. The high count means E tiles are easy to draw but worth only 1 point each."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many tiles are in a standard Scrabble game?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"A standard English Scrabble game contains exactly 100 tiles: 98 letter tiles and 2 blank tiles. The letter tiles are distributed based on how frequently each letter appears in English, with common letters like E (12 tiles) having more copies than rare letters like Z (1 tile)."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why does knowing tile frequency matter for Scrabble strategy?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Knowing tile frequency helps with tile tracking (knowing what's left in the bag), rack balancing (understanding which letters you're likely to draw), and defensive play (predicting what opponents might have). Expert players memorize the full distribution to make informed decisions throughout the game."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Statistics</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Letter Frequency in Scrabble — Tile Distribution Guide</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>8 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Every Scrabble game starts with the same 100 tiles, but not all letters are created equal. Understanding how tiles are distributed — which letters appear frequently and which are rare — gives you a strategic edge in rack management, tile tracking, and predicting your opponent's plays. Here's the complete breakdown.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Complete Tile Distribution</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300">The standard English Scrabble set contains 100 tiles distributed across 27 categories (26 letters plus blanks):</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">100</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Total Tiles</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">98</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Letter Tiles</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Blank Tiles</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">187</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Total Point Value</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-3 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Letter</th>
              <th class="px-3 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Count</th>
              <th class="px-3 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-3 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Letter</th>
              <th class="px-3 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Count</th>
              <th class="px-3 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">A</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">9</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">1</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">N</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">6</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">1</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">B</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">2</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">3</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">O</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">8</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">1</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">C</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">2</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">3</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">P</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">2</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">3</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">D</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">4</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">2</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">Q</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">1</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-amber-400 font-bold">10</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">E</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">12</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">1</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">R</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">6</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">1</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">F</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">2</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">4</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">S</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">4</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">1</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">G</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">3</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">2</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">T</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">6</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">1</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">H</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">2</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">4</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">U</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">4</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">1</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">I</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">9</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">1</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">V</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">2</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">4</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">J</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">1</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-amber-400 font-bold">8</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">W</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">2</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">4</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">K</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">1</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">5</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">X</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">1</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-amber-400 font-bold">8</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">L</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">4</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">1</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">Y</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">2</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">4</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">M</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">2</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">3</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-white font-mono">Z</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-gray-300">1</td><td class="px-3 py-2 text-amber-400 font-bold">10</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Frequency Tiers</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300">Tiles fall into distinct frequency groups that determine their strategic value:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🟢 High Frequency (6-12 tiles)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">E(12), A(9), I(9), O(8), N(6), R(6), T(6) — These form the backbone of most words. You'll draw them constantly.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔵 Medium Frequency (3-4 tiles)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">D(4), L(4), S(4), U(4), G(3) — Strategically important. S is the most valuable despite its low point value.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🟡 Low Frequency (2 tiles)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">B(2), C(2), F(2), H(2), M(2), P(2), V(2), W(2), Y(2) — Mid-value tiles. Duplicates hurt rack flexibility.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔴 Single Tiles (1 each)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">J(1), K(1), Q(1), X(1), Z(1) — High-value but rare. Once played, they're gone forever.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategic Implications</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300">Understanding frequency transforms how you make decisions throughout the game:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Tile Tracking</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Know what's been played to predict remaining tiles. If all 12 E's are gone, vowel-heavy words become impossible.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Rack Balance</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Aim for 4 consonants and 3 vowels. Frequency knowledge helps predict what you'll likely draw after exchanging.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Hoarding Rare Tiles</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Don't hold Q, X, or Z hoping for premium squares. Their rarity means opportunities are limited — play them when you can.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Ignoring Vowel Count</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">42 of 98 letter tiles are vowels (43%). Ignoring this ratio leads to unplayable racks.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">The letters in <span class="text-white font-medium">ETAOINSR</span> account for 68 of 98 letter tiles (69%). If you can't make a word from these letters, your rack is probably imbalanced.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Points vs Frequency Trade-off</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300">Scrabble's design creates an inverse relationship between frequency and point value:</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">1 pt</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">E, A, I, O, N, R, T, L, S, U</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2-4 pt</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">D, G, B, C, M, P, F, H, V, W, Y</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5-10 pt</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">K, J, X, Q, Z</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Track the S tiles:</span> Only 4 exist. Each S is worth far more than 1 point because it enables plurals and bingos. Never use S unless it gains 8+ extra points.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Memorize the singles:</span> J, K, Q, X, Z — once played, they're gone. This helps predict opponents' racks in the endgame.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Watch the blanks:</span> 2 blanks exist. They're the most powerful tiles despite being worth 0 points. If both are played, no more wild cards remain.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Use our Word Finder:</span> Enter your rack into our tool to see all possible words. Notice how common-letter racks produce more options than rare-letter racks.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/tile-tracking-guide" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Tile Tracking Guide</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/probability-based-play" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Probability-Based Play</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/highest-scoring-scrabble-words" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Highest Scoring Scrabble Words</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Try our free Scrabble Word Finder — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
